  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversees the BIM process in a design or construction organization.</li>\n  <li>Implementing and maintaining BIM standards, processes, and workflows.</li>\n  <li>Coordinating and collaborating with architects, engineers, contractors, and other project stakeholders to ensure accurate and timely delivery of BIM data</li>\n  <li>Training and educating project team members on BIM technology and workflows.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshooting and resolving BIM-related issues and conflicts.</li>\n  <li>Developing and maintaining BIM documentation and reports.</li>\n  <li>Ensuring compliance with BIM project requirements, standards, and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Ensuring that BIM execution plans are produced and maintained for each project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Relevant Diploma/Degree in Engineering field</li>\n  <li>Posses relevant certification recognized by BCA</li>\n  <li>Minimum 8 years of work experience in BIM.</li>\n  <li>Expert knowledge of BIM technology, software, and workflows.</li>\n  <li>Strong presentation, project management, team management and leadership skills.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in BIM software programs such as Revit, AutoCAD etc</li>\n  <li>Experience in MEP Projects is advantageous</li>\n</ul>",
